div.p:
And this certainely was Gods intent in the creating of our firſt fathers male, and female; becauſe, if it had not been for generations ſake, they might haue beene both created males: becauſe all things at their firſt creation were created in their greateſt perfection: if therefore the man bee more perfect then the woman, why ſhould they not both haue been created male, if it had not beene for their multiplication, by the ordinarie courſe of generation, eſpecially ſeeing God bleſſed them with theſe words, which ſignifie no leſſe; increaſe, or (as the Hebrue hath) fructifie, and multiply, eſpecially ſeeing (as the Philoſopher ſaith) generation is the moſt naturall action of life;
                  Ariſtotiles lib. 2. de anima, & lib. 4. meteor. 
                  yea then euery thing is in his perfect eſtate, when it is powerfull to bring forth another like to it ſelfe.
